  "prompt": "How do I connect my PC's internet to my Windows Phone via USB or via Bluetooth?",
  "response": "To share internet from your PC to a Windows Phone, you can use the following methods:\n\nUSB Tethering:\n1. Connect your Windows Phone to your PC using a USB cable\n2. On your PC:\n- Go to Network & Internet settings\n- Click \"Mobile Hotspot\"\n- Select your USB connection\n- Toggle \"Share my internet connection with other devices\"\n\nBluetooth Tethering:\n1. On your PC:\n- Go to Bluetooth settings\n- Pair your Windows Phone\n- Right-click the Bluetooth connection\n- Select \"Access internet connection\"\n\n2. On your Windows Phone:\n- Enable Bluetooth\n- Pair with your PC\n\nNote: The exact steps might vary slightly depending on your specific Windows version and phone model.\n\nAlternative options:\n- Use mobile Wi-Fi hotspot\n- Use cellular data directly\n- Use Wi-Fi sharing\n\nIf you're experiencing difficulties, ensure:\n- Latest Windows and phone updates are installed\n- Drivers are up to date\n- Bluetooth/USB connections are working properly\n\nWould you like more detailed instructions for your specific setup?",
